            <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-300">
                <div>
                    <h4 class="text-white font-medium">Does the GDPR apply to businesses in Kenya?</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Yes. Depending on the nature of the organisation's activities, the GDPR may apply to Kenyan businesses that offer goods or services to individuals located within the European Union or monitor their behaviour. We advise clients on determining whether the GDPR applies to their operations and how to achieve compliance.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="text-white font-medium">Does every organisation in Kenya need a Privacy Policy?</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Many organisations that collect personal information should maintain an appropriate Privacy Policy explaining how personal data is collected, used, stored, shared, and protected. The specific requirements depend on the nature of the organisation's activities and applicable legal obligations.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="text-white font-medium">Can personal data be transferred outside Kenya?</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Yes. Cross-border transfers are permitted subject to the requirements of the Data Protection Act, 2019 and applicable regulations. Appropriate safeguards should be implemented before personal information is transferred internationally.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="text-white font-medium">What should an organisation do after a data breach?</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Prompt legal assessment is essential. Organisations should investigate the incident, preserve relevant evidence, assess legal reporting obligations, implement remedial measures, and consider whether notification to affected individuals or regulators is required.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="text-white font-medium">Do foreign companies operating in Kenya need to comply with the Data Protection Act?</h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">In many cases, yes. Organisations processing personal data in connection with activities in Kenya may be subject to the requirements of the Data Protection Act, 2019, regardless of where the organisation is incorporated.</p>
                </div>
